tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured values are within or close to normal ranges. Glucose is slightly below normal, which may be due to fasting or pre-analytical factors and is not concerning in isolation. HbA1c indicates good long-term glycemic control. Renal, electrolyte, and lipid profiles are unremarkable. No significant laboratory abnormalities detected.
